


---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/main.astro';
---

<MainLayout 
  pageClass=""
  title="Terms & Conditions | Booking Policies - Glenugie Kennels"
  description="Read Glenugie Kennels' terms and conditions, booking policies, cancellation policy, and pet care requirements. Important information for all boarding guests."
  keywords="kennels terms and conditions, pet boarding policy, booking terms Peterhead, cancellation policy, kennel requirements"
  ogImage="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/69ea97152f20066bc07c2195/69f5d3c693d50ca27dfe5a52_PHOTO-2026-05-02-11-29-06.jpg"
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <Card>
          <CardContent className="prose prose-sm max-w-none p-8">
            <h2>Booking Terms and Conditions</h2>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

            <h3>1. Bookings and Reservations</h3>
            <p>
              All bookings are subject to availability and must be confirmed by Glenugie Kennels. 
              A deposit or full payment (as specified during booking) is required to secure your reservation.
            </p>

            <h3>2. Payment Terms</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>A £20 deposit is required to secure your booking</li>
              <li>The remaining balance must be paid upon drop-off or in advance</li>
              <li>We accept payment via credit/debit card through our secure Stripe payment system</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Cancellation Policy</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Cancellations made more than 14 days before check-in: Deposit is non-refundable but you will not be liable for the full payment</li>
              <li>Cancellations made less than 14 days before check-in: Deposit is non-refundable and you may be held liable for the full payment depending on circumstances</li>
              <li>No-shows: Full payment may be charged</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Check-in and Check-out</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Opening Hours: 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM Daily</li>
              <li>Drop Off Times: 2:00 PM - 5:00 PM Daily</li>
              <li>Pick Up Times: 10:00 AM - 12:00 PM</li>
              <li>Pick ups after 12:00 PM will incur additional charges</li>
              <li>Early or late arrivals must be arranged in advance</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5. Pet Requirements</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>All pets must be up to date with vaccinations (proof required)</li>
              <li>Dogs must be vaccinated against: Distemper, Hepatitis, Parvovirus, and Leptospirosis</li>
              <li>Kennel Cough vaccination is recommended but optional</li>
              <li>Cats must be vaccinated against: Cat Flu and Enteritis</li>
              <li>Pets must be treated for fleas and worms</li>
              <li>Aggressive or unsafe animals may be refused boarding</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>6. Health and Medical Care</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Pet owners must disclose any medical conditions or special requirements</li>
              <li>Medications must be provided in original containers with clear instructions</li>
              <li>In case of emergency, we will contact your designated veterinarian</li>
              <li>Owners are responsible for any veterinary costs incurred during the stay</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>7. Food and Special Diets</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Please provide your pet's regular food to avoid digestive upset</li>
              <li>Special dietary requirements must be clearly communicated</li>
              <li>Food should be labeled with your pet's name and feeding instructions</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>8. Personal Belongings</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>You may bring your pet's bedding, toys, and comfort items</li>
              <li>Please label all items with your pet's name</li>
              <li>We cannot be held responsible for lost or damaged personal items</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>9. Liability</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Glenugie Kennels takes every care with your pet, but cannot be held liable for illness, injury, or death of pets except where caused by our negligence</li>
              <li>Owners are liable for any damage caused by their pet to our facilities or other animals</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>10. Collection</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Pets must be collected by the agreed check-out date</li>
              <li>Additional boarding fees will apply for each day beyond the booked period</li>
              <li>Pets not collected within 7 days may be rehomed at our discretion</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>11. Privacy</h3>
            <p>
              We collect and store personal information solely for booking purposes and to provide 
              the best care for your pet. Your information will not be shared with third parties 
              except as required by law.
            </p>

            <h3>12. Changes to Terms</h3>
            <p>
              Glenugie Kennels reserves the right to modify these terms and conditions at any time. 
              Changes will be posted on our website and apply to future bookings.
            </p>

            <h3>13. Contact Information</h3>
            <p>
              For questions about these terms or your booking, please contact us:<br>
              Email: info@glenugiekennels.co.uk<br>
              Phone: +44 (0) 1234 567890
            </p>

            <div class="bg-muted p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
              <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Acceptance of Terms</p>
              <p class="text-sm">
                By making a booking with Glenugie Kennels, you acknowledge that you have read, 
                understood, and agree to be bound by these terms and conditions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </CardContent>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</MainLayout>



